{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id62bc5cfb-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s3417"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3417"},"text":"§ 3417.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Assignment of Federal personnel to State Indian economic development programs","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any State with an economic development program targeted to Indian tribes shall be eligible to receive, at no cost to the State, such Federal personnel assignments as the Secretary, in accordance with the applicable provisions of the Intergovernmental Personnel Act of 1970 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s4701"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 4701","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], may deem appropriate to help ensure the success of such program."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id62bc5cfc-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/477/s16"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–477, § 16","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 18, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/2306"},"text":"106 Stat. 2306","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 16, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/93"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–93","children":[],"tail":", 16(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/2036"},"text":"131 Stat. 2036","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id62bc5cfd-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id62bc5cfe-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id62bc5cff-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Intergovernmental Personnel Act of 1970, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/648"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–648","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 1971","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1909"},"text":"84 Stat. 1909","children":[],"tail":", which enacted sections 3371 to 3376 of Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, and chapter 62 (§ 4701 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s1304"},"text":"section 1304 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s246"},"text":"section 246 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", repealed sections 1881 to 1888 of Title 7, Agriculture, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s869b"},"text":"section 869b of Title 20","children":[],"tail":", Education, and enacted provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3371"},"text":"section 3371 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s4701"},"text":"section 4701 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id62bc5d00-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/477/s16"},"text":"